	<font size="-1"><b>The Best in Consumer Technology Design and Engineering</b></font>

	<p>Las Vegas, Nev. - Jan, 6 2000
	<BR>
	Attendees to the 2000 International CES,  held today through Sunday, January 9, in Las Vegas, can see the winning  product entries in the much anticipated Innovations 2000 design contest  sponsored by the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) and endorsed by the  Industrial Designers Society of America (IDSA) and the Consumer Electronics  Society of the Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE). The  contest’s winning products are on display at the Sands Expo and Convention  Center, and the “Best of Showcase” entries—the best of the best—also appear  in the Grand Lobby of the Las Vegas Convention Center. <P>
As the most widely renowned consumer technology awards program, Innovations  recognizes the best designed and engineered products in the categories of  accessibility, audio, blank media, computer hardware and software,  electronic gaming, home data networking, integrated home systems, home  appliances, home theater, online/Internet, mobile electronics, mobile  office, personal electronics, photographic equipment, retail resource,  satellite systems, small office/home office, specialty/high-end audio,  telephones, video and wireless communications. <P>
Demonstrating a true sense of imagination and excellence within the consumer  technology industry, the Best of Showcase winners are: <P>
